So I think your project should input **Handler** like `example.FunctionConfiguration`, however, I can&#39;t build the spring sample project successfully as I&#39;m really new to AWS Lamda, and there are some errors in the log.


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/TV7ld.png

This is AWS Toolkit for IntelliJ&#39;s problem. The plugin is only accepting the handler if it is in your project source root. so you can&#39;t use Spring Cloud Function&#39;s `handleRequest`.

To solve that, as answered above, you need to implement or extend requestHandler. For example :

```
public class HandlerWrapper extends FunctionInvoker{
	public void invokerWrapper(InputStream input, OutputStream output, Context context) throws IOException {
		this.handleRequest(input, output, context);
	}
}
```

Then set `HandlerWrapper::invokerWrapper` as a handler.

